red to raise an availability error and the other two returning valid data; assert run completes, report contains `data unavailable` only for failed section, and process does not abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness is about summary quality/faithfulness, which depends on real model output behavior; deterministic stubs would mask hallucination/omission errors. MOCK-HIDE: replacing generator with fixed text can always pass format checks while missing true semantic fidelity failures. MULTI-STEP: single model judgment step, so Agentic (not Workflow). REJECTION-GATE: Integration rejected because behavior text requires 'accurately represents key values,' which is output-quality validation, not just routing/retry/payload wiring.","test_description":"Feed representative weekly input datasets with known key metrics/issues/deployments into the real summary-generation model, evaluate generated narrative for factual inclusion/correctness against a rubric (or model-graded factuality checks), and run multiple trials to detect non-deterministic omissions/drift.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: this explicitly requires end-to-end behavior with real external services/infrastructure (source APIs plus email delivery/inbox reception), which exceeds in-process wiring. MOCK-HIDE: mocked mail transport could pass while DNS/TLS/auth/provider delivery failures remain invisible. LLM-DEP: assertion is inbox delivery correctness, not model quality; Agentic not required as minimum for this behavior. REJECTION-GATE: Workflow rejected because behavior does not require validating multiple agentic decisions, only end-to-end system delivery.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled job in an environment using real reachable test endpoints (or realistic staging equivalents) and a real mailbox; verify message is received by configured recipient, with expected report artifact attached/body included.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: failure involves service unreachability plus cross-run persistence/retry across scheduled executions; this is sensitive to real process/OS/file behavior. MOCK-HIDE: pure in-process mocks can miss startup/reload and filesystem-path/permission/timing issues that appear between real runs. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: no model-quality dependence; not Workflow. REJECTION-GATE: Integration was considered but rejected because behavior text requires retry on 'next scheduled run,' implying real run boundary/state persistence beyond single in-process call graph.","test_description":"Run job once with mail endpoint intentionally unreachable; assert fallback file is created on disk with full report content. Trigger next scheduled execution in a fresh process after restoring mail reachability; assert persisted report is retried and successfully delivered, then cleared/marked sent.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.63,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.04}}]}
